        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=6766&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=The+Progression+of+EQ"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> My view of EQ's progression has been changing with the recent "class balancing" that has been driving forward so fast.  Back in the beginning the programers and the people in control were loyal to "The Vision", now this new set of programers are making lots of changes without proper testing.  Previously when changes were made they took forever but they were at least remotely tested, now everything is thrown out as fast as it possibly can.  In a way some of this is good as we are finally getting some issues addressed that have needed attention for a long time now, but overall this, in my opinion, is going to end up bad.</P><P>If you look at the progression of EQ with its expanions it is easy to see how the quality they oringinally had is breaking down.  Sure back in the old world there are plenty of pathing bugs and safe spots, hell back in the day you could stand on roof tops in the karanas and nuke HGs without repercussion etc.  Now look at kunark: more mobs summon to make up for pathing and around this time mobs start warping to you.  Velious became worse with pathing, making even kunark look good.  Now with luclin, pathing is a JOKE.  Go to any zone in luclin and you can find a pathing bug... hell look at katta, you can fear kite without fear there just because of the horrid pathing.  In a lot of areas in luclin/velious you dont even need to try, just backing into a corner is sometimes a safespot because the programming is THAT bad.</P><P>All these changes that the dev team is shoving out has caused repercussions due to lack of testing.  Remember that patch that came out and all the icons were messed up.  I was wearing a dwarf head on my ear slot and a sword for my robe.  Even better how about the new UI.  The new UI has caused a rediculous amount of problems.  Items are disappearing from bags (friends lost epic pieces).  The whole HTML in the new UI thing was incredible that they could overlook that and how they could just let it be an exploitable crashing bug.  The new bug where custom UIs will not allow /bazaar.  Hell how about the bug Im sure most of you dont know about... a major reason for the patch a few night ago was because they introduced a duping bug with the new UI.  Go into bazaar and if its anything like Eci you will see idiot01 with 20 blue diamonds for 700 plat each while you have the other person who got the BD legit trying to sell for 1500.</P><P>How about breaking chardok quests.  I finally found angry up, turned in the note and he went and made his shout to the zone then he despawns in place... I sit there for a while and warlord never shows up.  Great so I wait a month and the GMs wont give me my note to sarkgus back so I have to request shady.  Oh but wait shady isnt even spawning.  So they finally fix angry a month later but shady STILL isnt spawning.  Now I got shady finally so now i have to compete with the other hundred people that are backflow from them both being broken for over a month.  I know other quests were broken also such as the 9th coldain ring war with dorigan (or however you spell it).  </P><P>This huge lack of testing is incredible.  What is the test server even for?  How many patches do we need in one week?  I mean sure all these patches have been nice and my guild has gotten a shot at a few more uber mobs just because they are spawning so often with all these patches.</P><P>Sure this is a rant, why not.  So let the flames roll.</P><P></P><P>By the way I disagree with all those of you who say necros are 100% broken, because we arent.  Anyone with any skill can do more for most exp groups than most other classes.  We still are broken on raids, but that is changing.</P><P>Nemth Fleshmangler<BR>Warlock and Officer of Final Companions on Eci<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59702" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59702</a></P><P>Edited by - Nemth Fleshmangler on 08/03/2002  15:12:38</font></td>

      </tr>

