         Your RIGHT. Things are getting better for us.</P><P>1. The Vision Team & Kelly Flock were fired. Gordon no longer leads the Live Team & I've yet to hear word one about George Scotto.</P><P>2. Night Time Spell restrictions: Tossed in the Trash.</P><P>2. Life Taps Land (re: our Patition last year but things got a little better for us on Raids).</P><P>3. Un-Nerfing Pets a bit. We may never get back our 49 Meat Grinder but atleast the Warlocks are longer calling up GREEN Pets.</P><P>4. The Bazaar finally came online & much fun is being had by all. Anyplace where a Necromancer can buy a Fugi Tunic for 75 PP simply can NOT be all bad.</P><P>Testing in general has always been a bad point with Verant. Look at all the fun we had with SOL. Verant seems focused on Content rather than fixing EQ. Else why would we still be attacked through walls in the Old World & Kunark?</P><P>I would not kick the current Programing Team just yet. We just might get luckey & get the FS Dagger Bug back & DOT Stacking as a welcome screw up.</P><P>Now I'll go Bark at the Moon!</P><P>Mags</P><P>Magisterdark Shadowquester,<BR>37 Teir'Dal Necromancer,<BR>Solusek Ro Server</P><P><img src="http://www.gbsu-usa.net/boss/respect.gif" border=0></P><P>BURN THEM ALIVE! ALIVE!!<BR>Victim of the Vision</P><P>Screwed since February 10, 1999. What's your excuse?<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
